season.info:
A *season* is the span of time, of usually 6 months where players compete for the top 10 slots on the money or reputation leaderboard. The winners will get badges and prizes based on their seasonal performance.
This is to allow a more competitive frame (before, money was pretty much stale) and to make the game a bit more fun.
You can access seasonal stuff using `-season`. Commands like profile, mine, fish and balance will require it, while games, loot, daily and reputation will give money/rep to both your global and seasonal profile.
season.info_2:
The current season is **%1$s** and **%2$s** players are currently taking part on it!

The fun begins, check `~>leaderboard money -season`; `~>leaderboard rep -season` and `~>leaderboard games -season`.
Game on! <3
Thanks for enjoying Mantaro.

make.start_text:
%1$sPradėtas **"`%2$s` pasirinktinės komandos kūrimas"**!
Parašyk `&~>stop`, kad sustabdytum kūrimą **neišsaugojant duomenų**.
Parašyk `&~>save`, kad sustabdytum kūrimą ir **išsaugotum naują komandą**. Išsiųsk bet kokį tekstą, prasidedantį `&`, kad pridėtum **naują komandos atsakymą**. Naudok `~>nsfw`, kad pažymėtum šią komandą kaip NDA ir atvirkštiniam variantui - `~>sfw`.
Šis interaktyvus procesas pasibaigs po 60 sekundžių neaktyvumo neišsaugojant duomenų.

inventory.brief:
**%1$s's item collection** %2$s

*For a detailed version, use `~>inventory -info`. Enjoy your day!*
inventory.calculate: %1$s%2$s gaus **%3$d kreditų**, jeigu parduos visus savo daiktus.
inventory.brief_notice: You can use `~>inventory -brief` to get a mobile friendly version.

cast.item_not_cast: %1$sYou cannot cast this item. You can check `~>cast ls` for a list of castable items. If the item name has spaces, wrap the name in quotes.
cast.not_enough_money: %1$sYou don't have enough money to cast this. **(Cost: %2$s)**
cast.no_item: %1$sYou don't have the necessary item *%2$s* to proceed with this cast.
cast.not_enough_items: %1$sYou don't have enough of item *%2$s* to proceed. **(Needed: %3$s, Current: %4$s)**

cast.item_broke: Sadly, your wrench broke in the process, but you got your item!
cast.too_many: %1$sYou'd have more than 5000 of this item if you proceed. Try casting less of this object?

cast.not_enough_wrench_level: %1$sYour wrench is not powerful enough to cast this item. Maybe specify a more powerful one? *Wrench level: %2$s, Required level: %3$s*. Example: `~>cast "star pick" "comet wrench"`
cast.too_many_amount: %1$sYou can't cast that many of this item at once! Limit: %2$s, Attempt: %3$s. A sparkle wrench makes the limit double! Unless you're already using one.

ls.desc:
This is a list of the items you can cast using `~>cast`. You have to use the full name or the short name to cast it (example: `~>cast diamond pickaxe` or `~>cast diamond p` works)
**Casting has a cost of half the price of the item. The casting price will be shown down below.**

cast.dust: %1$sYou cannot cast with such a dusty inventory! *(Dust level: %2$s%%)*. Why not clean it up using `~>useitem mop`?
cast.wrench_multiple_use: Tip: *You can't use the wrench you are trying to cast with as ingredient!*

price.collectible: %1$sThis is a collectible item. (Sell value: %2$d credits)
price.success: %1$sThe market value of %2$s**%3$s** is %4$s credits to buy it and you can get %5$s credits if you sell it.

buy.non_existent: %1$sYou cannot buy an non-existent item. If you're lost, you can try typing the short name or wrapping the name in quotes. Also, the item amount goes before the item name, example: `~>market buy 15 energy`

buy.success: %1$sBought %2$,d %3$s for %4$,d credits successfully. You now have %5$,d credits.

pet.explanation:
Pets are a useful companion in currency!
They help you gain more money, loot more, find random stuff on mine, chop trees, and even catch fish. The higher the level, the higher the rewards!
Getting the right pet for your activities is important, so make sure to check the type and abilities of the pet you want to choose!
Remember that you need to feed your pet and give it water, aswell as let it rest and charge up in energy every once in a while, just like a real pet! You can even pat it :)
For more help, use `~>help pet` and `~>pet list` for a list of pets.

birthday_enable.warning_3: Additionally the birthday cache (what is used to store them) is only updated every 23 hours. Meaning if you set your birthday today to tomorrow to test this announcer it will **not** work.
